body:
## Problem

The remote coding agent prompt file overlay was never visible to users, even when remote coding agents were available through extensions. The overlay widget exists and is fully implemented, but the `enableRemoteCodingAgentPromptFileOverlay` context key was never being set to `true`, preventing the UI from appearing.

## Root Cause

The overlay visibility logic in `PromptCodingAgentActionOverlay._updateVisibility()` requires three conditions:

```typescript
const shouldBeVisible = !!(
  isPromptFile && 
  enableRemoteCodingAgentPromptFileOverlay &&  // ❌ Always false - never initialized
  hasRemoteCodingAgent
);
```

While `hasRemoteCodingAgent` is properly managed by `RemoteCodingAgentsService`, the `enableRemoteCodingAgentPromptFileOverlay` context key had no initialization mechanism.

## Solution

Added a new workbench contribution `RemoteCodingAgentContextContribution` that:

1. **Adds configuration setting**: `chat.remoteCodingAgent.promptFileOverlay.enabled` (defaults to `true`)
2. **Initializes context key**: Sets `enableRemoteCodingAgentPromptFileOverlay` based on user configuration  
3. **Responds to changes**: Updates context key when configuration changes

```typescript
class RemoteCodingAgentContextContribution extends Disposable implements IWorkbenchContribution {
  constructor(
    @IContextKeyService private readonly contextKeyService: IContextKeyService,
    @IConfigurationService private readonly configurationService: IConfigurationService,
  ) {
    super();
    this.updateContextKey();
    this._register(this.configurationService.onDidChangeConfiguration(e => {
      if (e.affectsConfiguration('chat.remoteCodingAgent.promptFileOverlay.enabled')) {
        this.updateContextKey();
      }
    }));
  }

  private updateContextKey(): void {
    const isEnabled = this.configurationService.getValue<boolean>('chat.remoteCodingAgent.promptFileOverlay.enabled');
    ChatContextKeys.enableRemoteCodingAgentPromptFileOverlay.bindTo(this.contextKeyService).set(isEnabled);
  }
}
```

## User Impact

**Before**: Copilot coding agent overlay never appeared on `.prompt.md` files  
**After**: Overlay appears with "🔗 Delegate to Copilot coding agent" button when remote coding agents are available

Users can now:
- See the overlay button on prompt files when remote coding agents are registered
- Click to delegate their prompt to available coding agents  
- Configure the feature via `chat.remoteCodingAgent.promptFileOverlay.enabled` setting

## Testing

Added comprehensive unit tests covering:
- Context key initialization from configuration
- Configuration change handling
- Default value behavior

The fix is minimal (31 lines) and surgical - it only adds the missing initialization without modifying existing overlay logic.

